Who is it who doesn't know here?

00:33:56.220 --> 00:33:58.950 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: It's generational change
that you're talking about here

00:33:58.950 --> 00:34:00.270 align:middle line:10%
that we're going through.

00:34:00.270 --> 00:34:01.275 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, we
have to speed it up now.

00:34:01.275 --> 00:34:01.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You're
speeding it up, yes.

00:34:01.860 --> 00:34:03.526 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: It's
been long enough now.

00:34:03.526 --> 00:34:08.400 align:middle line:84%
I think women-- women, back in
1921, we got the right to vote.

00:34:08.400 --> 00:34:11.820 align:middle line:10%
And the suffragettes such
as Elizabeth Cady Stanton,

00:34:11.820 --> 00:34:14.130 align:middle line:10%
Susan B. Anthony,
and others assumed

00:34:14.130 --> 00:34:17.211 align:middle line:10%
we would just flood the system
