00:37:12.120 --> 00:37:13.440 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:37:13.440 --> 00:37:15.690 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And in the
history of the United States,

00:37:15.690 --> 00:37:19.050 align:middle line:10%
we were born of the
notion of possibility.

00:37:19.050 --> 00:37:21.030 align:middle line:10%
Now, that notion of
possibility that we

00:37:21.030 --> 00:37:24.750 align:middle line:10%
could be founded as a democracy,
that we could be founded

00:37:24.750 --> 00:37:28.841 align:middle line:10%
on a notion which is truly an
exceptional notion, that it

00:37:28.841 --> 00:37:30.340 align:middle line:10%
didn't matter who
your parents were.

00:37:30.340 --> 00:37:31.800 align:middle line:10%
It didn't matter what
your education was.

00:37:31.800 --> 00:37:33.480 align:middle line:10%
It didn't matter
what your money was,

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:38.880 align:middle line:10%
that we would create a context
where from our perspective,

00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:41.790 align:middle line:10%
self-actualization
would be possible.

00:37:41.790 --> 00:37:44.760 align:middle line:10%
That is what it stood
for, novus ordo seclorum,

00:37:44.760 --> 00:37:46.140 align:middle line:10%
new order of the ages.

00:37:46.140 --> 00:37:47.527 align:middle line:10%
This was not only radical.

00:37:47.527 --> 00:37:48.360 align:middle line:10%
It was radical then.

00:37:48.360 --> 00:37:49.470 align:middle line:10%
It's radical now.

00:37:49.470 --> 00:37:52.740 align:middle line:10%
It was not only radical
in political terms.

00:37:52.740 --> 00:37:55.740 align:middle line:10%
It's radical in philosophical
and spiritual terms.

00:37:55.740 --> 00:37:57.990 align:middle line:10%
It's truly to create
a space on Earth

00:37:57.990 --> 00:38:02.040 align:middle line:10%
to the best of our ability where
the human soul could express

00:38:02.040 --> 00:38:03.930 align:middle line:10%
itself however it wishes.

00:38:03.930 --> 00:38:07.750 align:middle line:10%
So democracy represents
a spiritual impulse.

00:38:07.750 --> 00:38:10.110 align:middle line:10%
Now, from the
beginning, as we know,

00:38:10.110 --> 00:38:11.904 align:middle line:10%
it's not news to anyone
most of the signers

00:38:11.904 --> 00:38:13.320 align:middle line:10%
of the Declaration
of Independence

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:16.230 align:middle line:10%
were themselves slave owners.

00:38:16.230 --> 00:38:20.010 align:middle line:10%
And by the way, the irony of
this was not lost on them.

00:38:20.010 --> 00:38:22.890 align:middle line:10%
Jefferson's line, "I
tremble for my country

00:38:22.890 --> 00:38:26.040 align:middle line:10%
when I consider God is just
and that his justice shall not

00:38:26.040 --> 00:38:27.550 align:middle line:10%
sleep forever."

00:38:27.550 --> 00:38:31.950 align:middle line:10%
So the political narrative, the
journey of the United States

00:38:31.950 --> 00:38:34.860 align:middle line:10%
has been and continues to be--
in this generation as much

00:38:34.860 --> 00:38:36.210 align:middle line:10%
as any other--

00:38:36.210 --> 00:38:38.670 align:middle line:10%
between the forces
represented by people

00:38:38.670 --> 00:38:42.810 align:middle line:10%
who would like to limit
the actual embodiment

00:38:42.810 --> 00:38:46.380 align:middle line:10%
or full manifestation of the
extraordinary possibilities

00:38:46.380 --> 00:38:49.080 align:middle line:10%
of democracy versus
those who would say, no,

00:38:49.080 --> 00:38:50.170 align:middle line:10%
let's make it real.

00:38:50.170 --> 00:38:51.810 align:middle line:10%
It's not just white people.

00:38:51.810 --> 00:38:53.910 align:middle line:10%
It's not just men.

00:38:53.910 --> 00:38:55.680 align:middle line:10%
It's not just this group.

00:38:55.680 --> 00:38:56.670 align:middle line:10%
It's everybody.

00:38:56.670 --> 00:39:00.976 align:middle line:10%
If God created everyone equal,
if all are created equal,

00:39:00.976 --> 00:39:02.100 align:middle line:10%
that doesn't just mean men.

00:39:02.100 --> 00:39:04.140 align:middle line:10%
That doesn't just mean whites.

00:39:04.140 --> 00:39:05.861 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't just mean anything.

00:39:05.861 --> 00:39:07.110 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't just mean the rich.

00:39:07.110 --> 00:39:08.890 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't just mean
straight people.

00:39:08.890 --> 00:39:11.348 align:middle line:10%
And I think one of the frontiers
for American understanding

00:39:11.348 --> 00:39:15.600 align:middle line:10%
is that we really get clearly,
it doesn't just mean Americans

00:39:15.600 --> 00:39:17.730 align:middle line:10%
if God created everyone equal.

00:39:17.730 --> 00:39:20.610 align:middle line:10%
And so it is a
spiritual expansion

00:39:20.610 --> 00:39:22.620 align:middle line:10%
represented by
our fuller embrace

00:39:22.620 --> 00:39:24.660 align:middle line:10%
of what democracy actually is.

00:39:24.660 --> 00:39:26.104 align:middle line:10%
And once again,
in our generation

00:39:26.104 --> 00:39:28.270 align:middle line:10%
as much as any other, there
are those who would say,

00:39:28.270 --> 00:39:31.091 align:middle line:10%
whoa, whoa, whoa, we don't
want everybody voting.

00:39:31.091 --> 00:39:33.550 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHTER]

00:39:33.550 --> 00:39:35.260 align:middle line:10%
And things like that.

00:39:35.260 --> 00:39:38.320 align:middle line:10%
We have, as we know, over
the last few decades,

00:39:38.320 --> 00:39:40.900 align:middle line:10%
through corporate subsidies,
tax breaks, et cetera--

00:39:40.900 --> 00:39:44.194 align:middle line:10%
we have actually accumulated--
we have systematically

00:39:44.194 --> 00:39:45.610 align:middle line:10%
taken the majority
of the material

00:39:45.610 --> 00:39:48.310 align:middle line:10%
resources of the
country and moved

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:51.040 align:middle line:10%
them very systematically into
what represents basically

00:39:51.040 --> 00:39:54.490 align:middle line:10%
the hands of the very few so
that we now have 1% controlling

00:39:54.490 --> 00:39:56.726 align:middle line:10%
42% of our wealth.

00:39:56.726 --> 00:39:58.850 align:middle line:10%
When we think of the first
principles of the United

00:39:58.850 --> 00:40:01.690 align:middle line:10%
States, we think of
the Constitution.

00:40:01.690 --> 00:40:03.760 align:middle line:10%
We think of the
Declaration of Independence

00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:09.580 align:middle line:10%
and also Lincoln's famous adage
in the Gettysburg Address,

00:40:09.580 --> 00:40:12.440 align:middle line:10%
that these men at Gettysburg
had not died in vain,

00:40:12.440 --> 00:40:14.440 align:middle line:10%
but so that there could
be a rebirth of freedom,

00:40:14.440 --> 00:40:17.470 align:middle line:10%
and then his extraordinary
phrase that government

00:40:17.470 --> 00:40:24.160 align:middle line:10%
of the people, by the
people, and for the people

00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:25.600 align:middle line:10%
would not perish from the earth.

00:40:25.600 --> 00:40:27.850 align:middle line:10%
Well, I think it's really
important for all of us

00:40:27.850 --> 00:40:29.110 align:middle line:10%
to be very clear.

00:40:29.110 --> 00:40:33.040 align:middle line:10%
If we are going to change the
social agreement in the United

00:40:33.040 --> 00:40:36.710 align:middle line:10%
States of America from
government of the people,

00:40:36.710 --> 00:40:38.470 align:middle line:10%
by the people,
and for the people

00:40:38.470 --> 00:40:41.649 align:middle line:10%
to government of a few of the
people, by a few of the people,

00:40:41.649 --> 00:40:44.190 align:middle line:10%
for a few of the people, we need
to have a debate about that.

00:40:44.190 --> 00:40:45.160 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHTER]

00:40:45.160 --> 00:40:47.100 align:middle line:10%
[APPLAUSE]

00:40:47.100 --> 00:40:48.560 align:middle line:90%


00:40:48.560 --> 00:40:51.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Since you are at the
forefront of infusing politics

00:40:51.560 --> 00:40:54.080 align:middle line:84%
and spirituality
together, how do you

00:40:54.080 --> 00:40:57.080 align:middle line:84%
propose to bring that
conversation into Congress?

00:40:57.080 --> 00:40:59.840 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well,
spirituality is simply the quest

00:40:59.840 --> 00:41:01.760 align:middle line:90%
for living from the heart.

00:41:01.760 --> 00:41:05.510 align:middle line:84%
And the problem with
our political system,

00:41:05.510 --> 00:41:07.430 align:middle line:84%
with our civilization
is that we are

00:41:07.430 --> 00:41:09.410 align:middle line:84%
ordered according to
economic principle rather

00:41:09.410 --> 00:41:11.000 align:middle line:90%
than humanitarian values.

00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:13.770 align:middle line:84%
We make money rather than
love the bottom line.

00:41:13.770 --> 00:41:17.417 align:middle line:84%
And because of the
undue influence

00:41:17.417 --> 00:41:19.250 align:middle line:84%
of money on our system,
because of the flood

00:41:19.250 --> 00:41:23.180 align:middle line:84%
of corporate lobbyists and
other wealthy individuals who

00:41:23.180 --> 00:41:25.820 align:middle line:84%
are able to affect our
system the way they are,

00:41:25.820 --> 00:41:27.020 align:middle line:90%
I want to be someone--

00:41:27.020 --> 00:41:28.490 align:middle line:84%
and there are
others, by the way.

00:41:28.490 --> 00:41:30.906 align:middle line:84%
It's not like there aren't
people in the US Congress today

00:41:30.906 --> 00:41:32.900 align:middle line:84%
who are standing up for
humanitarian values,

00:41:32.900 --> 00:41:33.860 align:middle line:90%
because there are.

00:41:33.860 --> 00:41:37.340 align:middle line:10%
I want, however, to add my
voice in the most passionate way

00:41:37.340 --> 00:41:39.710 align:middle line:10%
to those who are saying
that the moneyed interests

00:41:39.710 --> 00:41:42.380 align:middle line:10%
of a small sector of
our society should not

00:41:42.380 --> 00:41:44.332 align:middle line:10%
be placed over the
interests of our children

00:41:44.332 --> 00:41:46.790 align:middle line:10%
who need to go to preschool,
our children who need a better

00:41:46.790 --> 00:41:50.030 align:middle line:10%
education, our children
who need quality food that

00:41:50.030 --> 00:41:56.450 align:middle line:10%
is uncorrupted by GMOs, by our
children who need quality air.

00:41:56.450 --> 00:41:58.550 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you an
example of something

00:41:58.550 --> 00:42:00.140 align:middle line:90%
that I found just shocking.

00:42:00.140 --> 00:42:02.300 align:middle line:84%
We have no air quality
safety standards

00:42:02.300 --> 00:42:04.550 align:middle line:90%
in our public schools, Lisa.

00:42:04.550 --> 00:42:08.780 align:middle line:84%
And 40% of all teachers and
students at our public schools

00:42:08.780 --> 00:42:12.320 align:middle line:84%
are already known to
be adversely affected

00:42:12.320 --> 00:42:16.430 align:middle line:84%
in their respiratory
systems, asthma, et cetera.

00:42:16.430 --> 00:42:21.830 align:middle line:84%
So we continue to give
subsidies and tax breaks

00:42:21.830 --> 00:42:24.230 align:middle line:84%
to the wealthiest
Americans, which

00:42:24.230 --> 00:42:28.010 align:middle line:84%
is sucking money and economic
resources out of our budget

00:42:28.010 --> 00:42:31.537 align:middle line:84%
that we could be using on
taking care of our people.

00:42:31.537 --> 00:42:33.870 align:middle line:10%
That's what Lincoln meant by
a government of the people,

00:42:33.870 --> 00:42:35.849 align:middle line:10%
by the people, and for
the people, this idea

00:42:35.849 --> 00:42:37.640 align:middle line:10%
that if we give the
money to the very rich,

00:42:37.640 --> 00:42:40.130 align:middle line:10%
that that will create jobs.

00:42:40.130 --> 00:42:41.120 align:middle line:90%
It's just an illusion.

00:42:41.120 --> 00:42:42.050 align:middle line:90%
It's not even true.

00:42:42.050 --> 00:42:43.970 align:middle line:84%
The people who say it
know it's not true.

00:42:43.970 --> 00:42:45.950 align:middle line:84%
Because jobs come
from the middle

00:42:45.950 --> 00:42:48.770 align:middle line:84%
class, people who are
thriving in their lives.

00:42:48.770 --> 00:42:50.870 align:middle line:84%
The majority of
jobs in America come

00:42:50.870 --> 00:42:54.350 align:middle line:84%
from situations like yours,
where you had this television

00:42:54.350 --> 00:42:56.420 align:middle line:90%
situation, a radio station.

00:42:56.420 --> 00:42:57.950 align:middle line:84%
This is where jobs
are created from.

00:42:57.950 --> 00:43:01.010 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I mean, I
also think about OSHA,

00:43:01.010 --> 00:43:03.170 align:middle line:84%
the environmental
organization that does go in.

00:43:03.170 --> 00:43:05.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I know some
people who work for OSHA.

00:43:05.550 --> 00:43:07.170 align:middle line:84%
And they're, again,
middle class,

00:43:07.170 --> 00:43:09.620 align:middle line:90%
working citizens, hardworking.

00:43:09.620 --> 00:43:11.540 align:middle line:84%
One particularly has
an autistic child.

00:43:11.540 --> 00:43:15.650 align:middle line:84%
And there's a situation where
those people are trying to make

00:43:15.650 --> 00:43:18.180 align:middle line:84%
and penetrate the systems
that they sometimes cannot get

00:43:18.180 --> 00:43:18.980 align:middle line:90%
through to.

00:43:18.980 --> 00:43:21.310 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Exactly right,
because a lot of these--

00:43:21.310 --> 00:43:23.810 align:middle line:84%
it was Richard Nixon who set
up the Environmental Protection

00:43:23.810 --> 00:43:24.410 align:middle line:90%
Agency.

00:43:24.410 --> 00:43:25.578 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he was a
Republican president.

00:43:25.578 --> 00:43:26.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In the '60s, yeah.

00:43:26.130 --> 00:43:28.940 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: But the country
has gone so far to the right

00:43:28.940 --> 00:43:31.760 align:middle line:84%
now that what used to be the
right is now the far right,

00:43:31.760 --> 00:43:34.550 align:middle line:84%
and what used to be the left
in governmental functioning

00:43:34.550 --> 00:43:35.900 align:middle line:90%
is pretty centrist.

00:43:35.900 --> 00:43:38.750 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of these agencies
that were actually set up

00:43:38.750 --> 00:43:42.170 align:middle line:84%
with the purpose of
advocating for the people

00:43:42.170 --> 00:43:44.930 align:middle line:84%
against the excesses
of certain industries

00:43:44.930 --> 00:43:47.210 align:middle line:84%
now consider themselves
as having a dual role

00:43:47.210 --> 00:43:50.750 align:middle line:84%
at best and sometimes almost
completely to advocate

00:43:50.750 --> 00:43:52.430 align:middle line:90%
for those industries.

00:43:52.430 --> 00:43:54.670 align:middle line:84%
The government needs
to work for the people.

00:43:54.670 --> 00:43:57.770 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about a change
in the basic social contract

00:43:57.770 --> 00:44:00.216 align:middle line:84%
that every American has
the right to expect.

00:44:00.216 --> 00:44:02.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's government of
the people, by the people,

00:44:02.340 --> 00:44:03.260 align:middle line:90%
and for the people.

00:44:03.260 --> 00:44:05.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you used
to be a Democrat.

00:44:05.030 --> 00:44:07.531 align:middle line:84%
Now, you've swung towards the
center, the Independent Party.

00:44:07.531 --> 00:44:09.488 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: I've been
a Democrat all my life.

00:44:09.488 --> 00:44:11.597 align:middle line:10%
And if I win, I will
caucus with Democrats.

00:44:11.597 --> 00:44:12.680 align:middle line:10%
I have a Democrat's heart.

00:44:12.680 --> 00:44:14.930 align:middle line:10%
But I gotta tell you something.

00:44:14.930 --> 00:44:16.790 align:middle line:10%
We have got to have
a new conversation

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:18.740 align:middle line:10%
now because it's
become so corrupted,

00:44:18.740 --> 00:44:21.440 align:middle line:10%
Republican versus Democrat.

00:44:21.440 --> 00:44:23.907 align:middle line:10%
And the things that
upset me about money,

00:44:23.907 --> 00:44:25.490 align:middle line:10%
I'm concerned about
some of the places

00:44:25.490 --> 00:44:27.300 align:middle line:10%
where they're way
too much the same.

00:44:27.300 --> 00:44:31.250 align:middle line:84%
That's why I think if we have
20 independent candidates, if we

00:44:31.250 --> 00:44:34.340 align:middle line:84%
have 20 independent congressmen
in the US House, that

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:35.538 align:middle line:90%
will change everything.

00:44:35.538 --> 00:44:36.746 align:middle line:90%
So I believe that right now--

00:44:36.746 --> 00:44:37.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How many are there now?

00:44:37.890 --> 00:44:38.600 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well,
there aren't any.

00:44:38.600 --> 00:44:41.450 align:middle line:84%
There are two independent
senators, Bernie Sanders

00:44:41.450 --> 00:44:43.250 align:middle line:90%
and Angus King.

00:44:43.250 --> 00:44:45.170 align:middle line:84%
If we have independent
voices-- and there's

00:44:45.170 --> 00:44:49.100 align:middle line:84%
nothing about in our
constitution about two parties.

00:44:49.100 --> 00:44:50.570 align:middle line:90%
You know what I always say?

00:44:50.570 --> 00:44:54.500 align:middle line:84%
In some countries, they have
only two brands of toothpaste,

00:44:54.500 --> 00:44:56.780 align:middle line:84%
but 14 brands of
political party.

00:44:56.780 --> 00:44:59.750 align:middle line:84%
In our country, we
have so much choice

00:44:59.750 --> 00:45:02.750 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to toothpaste
and sneakers and T-shirts.

00:45:02.750 --> 00:45:04.000 align:middle line:10%
It's like we're not really--

00:45:04.000 --> 00:45:04.800 align:middle line:10%
hello.

00:45:04.800 --> 00:45:06.620 align:middle line:10%
It's not really penetrating
that even though we

00:45:06.620 --> 00:45:08.180 align:middle line:10%
have a lot of brands
of toothpaste,

00:45:08.180 --> 00:45:09.830 align:middle line:10%
we only have two brands
of political voice.

00:45:09.830 --> 00:45:11.420 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Well, every election
you see the red states

00:45:11.420 --> 00:45:12.440 align:middle line:10%
and blue states,
the red states--

00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:13.486 align:middle line:10%
and you don't see
the green states.

00:45:13.486 --> 00:45:15.777 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And yet, there's
something coming up from

00:45:15.777 --> 00:45:17.380 align:middle line:10%
the bottom of things,
from our hearts,

00:45:17.380 --> 00:45:20.060 align:middle line:10%
from our subconscious that wants
to have a conversation separate

00:45:20.060 --> 00:45:22.130 align:middle line:10%
from the one either one
of them are having--

00:45:22.130 --> 00:45:26.900 align:middle line:10%
a new kind of synthesis,
a new kind of bottom line,

00:45:26.900 --> 00:45:30.020 align:middle line:10%
a new kind of stepping into
a vision and possibility

00:45:30.020 --> 00:45:33.110 align:middle line:10%
that that system
does not account for.

00:45:33.110 --> 00:45:35.780 align:middle line:84%
So abolition didn't come
from a major political party.

00:45:35.780 --> 00:45:38.720 align:middle line:84%
Women's suffragettes didn't come
from a major political party.

00:45:38.720 --> 00:45:41.640 align:middle line:84%
Social security didn't even come
from a major political party.

00:45:41.640 --> 00:45:43.340 align:middle line:84%
So often in the
history of the United

00:45:43.340 --> 00:45:45.860 align:middle line:84%
States and our major
movements forward,

00:45:45.860 --> 00:45:47.870 align:middle line:84%
it was movements
that did not come

00:45:47.870 --> 00:45:49.550 align:middle line:90%
through the political parties.

00:45:49.550 --> 00:45:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Came from the people, and
then the political parties

00:45:52.200 --> 00:45:53.000 align:middle line:90%
came along.

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:55.083 align:middle line:84%
For us to expect the
political parties to lead us,

00:45:55.083 --> 00:45:58.040 align:middle line:84%
to really deliver us to the new
conversation, is naive at best.

00:45:58.040 --> 00:45:59.456 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: If anyone
could do it, you

00:45:59.456 --> 00:46:01.590 align:middle line:84%
could because you are
steeped in that conversation.

00:46:01.590 --> 00:46:02.930 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: I don't
know if I can, but we can.

00:46:02.930 --> 00:46:03.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, good point.

00:46:03.800 --> 00:46:04.883 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for saying that.

00:46:04.883 --> 00:46:07.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you do get
into Congress--

00:46:07.370 --> 00:46:11.250 align:middle line:84%
and I should say when you get
into Congress-- what would

00:46:11.250 --> 00:46:12.050 align:middle line:90%
you do?

00:46:12.050 --> 00:46:14.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what would
be your first step,

00:46:14.240 --> 00:46:16.910 align:middle line:84%
and where would you start
if you got into this seat?

00:46:16.910 --> 00:46:19.276 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, as I
said, what I will be saying

00:46:19.276 --> 00:46:21.650 align:middle line:84%
throughout this campaign and
if I have the honor of being

00:46:21.650 --> 00:46:24.410 align:middle line:84%
elected, I will certainly
live up to what I'm saying--

00:46:24.410 --> 00:46:26.630 align:middle line:84%
I will become involved
with everything

00:46:26.630 --> 00:46:29.540 align:middle line:84%
possible having to do with
the interim steps, all the way

00:46:29.540 --> 00:46:33.690 align:middle line:84%
up to and including the move
for a constitutional amendment

00:46:33.690 --> 00:46:36.380 align:middle line:84%
to get the influence of
money out of our politics.

00:46:36.380 --> 00:46:38.750 align:middle line:10%
And I will have a
platform that I will not

00:46:38.750 --> 00:46:41.030 align:middle line:10%
have if I'm not elected,
both within the Congress,

00:46:41.030 --> 00:46:42.530 align:middle line:10%
as well as throughout
the community,

00:46:42.530 --> 00:46:45.340 align:middle line:10%
in the country, the people
that I can talk to about that.

00:46:45.340 --> 00:46:47.090 align:middle line:84%
The derivative
issues, of course,

00:46:47.090 --> 00:46:48.674 align:middle line:84%
having to do with
mass incarceration,

00:46:48.674 --> 00:46:50.840 align:middle line:84%
having to do with the
corruption of our food supply,

00:46:50.840 --> 00:46:54.220 align:middle line:84%
having to do with preschool,
having to do with free college.

00:46:54.220 --> 00:46:56.570 align:middle line:84%
You have one major
political party

00:46:56.570 --> 00:46:58.955 align:middle line:84%
who just doesn't want
help these kids at all.

00:46:58.955 --> 00:47:00.830 align:middle line:84%
You have another major
political party trying

00:47:00.830 --> 00:47:02.570 align:middle line:90%
to lower the interest rates.

00:47:02.570 --> 00:47:05.510 align:middle line:84%
I think there should be free
college in this country.

00:47:05.510 --> 00:47:08.266 align:middle line:84%
Oregon is already-- for
the capable students

00:47:08.266 --> 00:47:09.890 align:middle line:84%
who live up to the
standards necessary.

00:47:09.890 --> 00:47:11.855 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Isn't that what
financial aid does?

00:47:11.855 --> 00:47:14.480 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: No, financial aid,
still you have to pay it back.

00:47:14.480 --> 00:47:16.100 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:47:16.100 --> 00:47:18.200 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Oregon has
already created a system

00:47:18.200 --> 00:47:22.550 align:middle line:10%
where we could enable
the kids who deserve it,

00:47:22.550 --> 00:47:24.680 align:middle line:10%
who worked for it, who
are keeping up that,

00:47:24.680 --> 00:47:26.180 align:middle line:10%
and then the system,
for instance, I

00:47:26.180 --> 00:47:29.600 align:middle line:10%
think that Oregon is trying
has to do with a 2% or 3%

00:47:29.600 --> 00:47:32.330 align:middle line:10%
that they would pay back, paying
it forward when they leave.

00:47:32.330 --> 00:47:33.230 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: I see.

00:47:33.230 --> 00:47:34.100 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON:
Because if you really

00:47:34.100 --> 00:47:35.840 align:middle line:10%
want to stimulate
your economy, what you

00:47:35.840 --> 00:47:37.880 align:middle line:10%
want more than anything
is more educated people.

00:47:37.880 --> 00:47:38.870 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Education, yes, yes.

00:47:38.870 --> 00:47:40.280 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And more
people who come out of school

00:47:40.280 --> 00:47:41.870 align:middle line:10%
ready to form their
own $6 million

00:47:41.870 --> 00:47:44.713 align:middle line:10%
company if they
put out the effort.

00:47:44.713 --> 00:47:46.254 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's the
way of our future.

00:47:46.254 --> 00:47:47.390 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: I think these
are the kinds of conversations

00:47:47.390 --> 00:47:48.306 align:middle line:90%
that I will be having.

00:47:48.306 --> 00:47:51.470 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: And now, what about
the Department of Peace?

00:47:51.470 --> 00:47:52.670 align:middle line:10%
Is it currently in place?

00:47:52.670 --> 00:47:53.090 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, yes.

00:47:53.090 --> 00:47:55.020 align:middle line:10%
When Dennis Kucinich
was a congressman,

00:47:55.020 --> 00:47:58.370 align:middle line:10%
he started the Department of
Peace campaign legislation.

00:47:58.370 --> 00:48:01.220 align:middle line:84%
And it is now taken
over by Barbara Lee.

00:48:01.220 --> 00:48:03.620 align:middle line:84%
It is now called the
Department of Peace building.

00:48:03.620 --> 00:48:06.530 align:middle line:84%
I would certainly be a
sponsor of that bill.

00:48:06.530 --> 00:48:09.590 align:middle line:84%
It's a very important bill that
I've been part of the campaign

00:48:09.590 --> 00:48:11.630 align:middle line:90%
to support that for years now.

00:48:11.630 --> 00:48:16.700 align:middle line:84%
It would be an executive
branch department

00:48:16.700 --> 00:48:19.820 align:middle line:84%
that articulates and
facilitates and researches

00:48:19.820 --> 00:48:22.430 align:middle line:84%
nonviolent problem
solving options

00:48:22.430 --> 00:48:25.880 align:middle line:84%
for both domestic and
international conflict.

00:48:25.880 --> 00:48:28.160 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we have the
Defense Department,

00:48:28.160 --> 00:48:29.716 align:middle line:84%
and we have the
State Department.

00:48:29.716 --> 00:48:31.340 align:middle line:10%
The Defense Department
could be likened

00:48:31.340 --> 00:48:33.200 align:middle line:10%
to visiting your surgeon.

00:48:33.200 --> 00:48:37.550 align:middle line:10%
If you need an invasive
surgery, you go to your doctor.

00:48:37.550 --> 00:48:41.150 align:middle line:10%
So if we feel that invasive
military measures are the best,

00:48:41.150 --> 00:48:42.980 align:middle line:10%
